                            <comment id="13462138" author="jesse_yates" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 21:08:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt; yeah, dev-support seems like a solid plan. We should also consider having a code-template as well so things like the license, etc. are always added. Accumulo folks did this and it really helps ensure good formatting, especially when the formatters are part of the codebase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13462171" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 21:49:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cool, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
